Chocolate Cassis Cake

Cake:
12 tbsp unsalted butter (1 1/2 sticks)
10 oz bittersweet chocolate, chopped
1/2 c unsweetened cocoa powder
6 tbsp creme de cassis liqueur
1 tsp vanilla
5 extra large eggs at room temp
1 c sugar
1/4 tsp kosher sa;t

Preheat oven to 350F. Spray a 9" round pringform pan with baking spray. Line the bottom of the pan with parchment paper and spray again. Melt the butter and chocoalte together in a heatproof bowl set over a pan of simmering water, stirring occasionally until smooth. Set aside to cool for 5 min. Whisk in the cocoa powder, cassis, and vanilla and set aside. In the bowl of an electric mixer fitted with the whisk attachment, beat the eggs, sugar, and salt on high for 3-5 min, until pale yellow and triple in volume. Pour the chocolate mixture into the egg mixture and carefully but thoroughly fold them together with a rubber spatula. Pour the batter into the prepared pan and bake for 35-40 min, until just barely set in the center. Allow to cool in the pan for 30 min and then release the sides of the pan. Invert the cake carefully onto a flat serving plate, remove the parchment paper, and cool completely.

Glaze:
6 oz bittersweet or semisweet chocoalte, chopped
1/4 c heavy cream
2-3 tbsp creme de cassis liqueur
1/2 tsp vanilla

Melt the chocolate and cream together in a heatproof bowl set over a pan of simmering water. Stir until smooth. Off the heat, whisk in the cassis and vanilla. Allow to cool for 10 min and spread over just the top of the cake.


To serve:
2 (1/2 pint) boxes fresh raspberries
1 pint fresh strawberries, hulled and thickly sliced
1/3 c sugar
1/3 c creme de cassis liqueur

15 min before serving, toss the berries gently with the sugar and liqueur, Cut the cake in wedges and serve with the berries on the side.
